def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Reorganize the codes and levels of the index
    index = data.index
    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) for i in clocs]
    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    # Handle hierarchical columns
    if isinstance(data.columns, MultiIndex):
        # If the columns are multi-level, unstack them using each level in clocs
        result = data
        for i in range(len(clocs)):
            val = clocs[i]
            result = result.unstack(val, fill_value=fill_value)
            clocs = [v if i > v else v - 1 for v in clocs]
        return result
    else:
        # Handle hierarchical index
        dummy_index = index.unstack(level=clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

        unstacked = data.unstack(level=clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

        return unstacked
